    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Bethamia, Forsyth Co. No. Ca.</placeName>
                <date>May 25th 1860</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia, Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My absence from home &amp;<lb/> the pressure of business awaiting me
                on my return have caused the delay<lb/> of my present answer &amp; remittance, for
                which I beg your pardon.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed please find a ten Dollar Bill of the People's<lb/> Bank
                    <placeName>Charleston, So. Ca.</placeName>, which is amount due you for
                your<lb/> Bible translation, Catechism &amp; <persName>Dias'</persName> letters all
                duly received in one<lb/> package through <persName>Adam's &amp; Co's</persName>
                Express. Although I intended<lb/> to get your Bible-translation after having
                effected my projected<lb/> &amp; early removal from here. I am glad that you have
                anticipated<lb/> my wish by sending the same at the time you did.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have not had as yet spare time to give the books the
                necessary<lb/> attention, but hope to be enabled to do it soon. From a
                superficial<lb/> perusal of some portions of the same I have been greatly benefitted
                &amp;<lb/> gratified &amp; I have already gained invaluable instruction. I
                en<lb/>tertain the pleasing hope to find there a satisfactory amount of<lb/>
                affirmative striking &amp; national explanations &amp; the true <hi rend="underline"
                    >references</hi> of<lb/> the 53th Chapter &amp; of the 121th verse of the 7th
                Chap. of <persName>Isaiah</persName><lb/> as well as of the 6 verse of the 12 Chapt.
                    of<persName> Zechariah</persName>
                <add>?</add><lb/> There is not the most remote doubt in my mind as to the wrong<lb/>
                &amp; <sic>permited</sic> application <add>&amp; reference</add> of them &amp;
                similar prophecies, which<lb/> christian commentators give to them, for the whole
                system of <add>the</add> christian</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>religion is hand upon contradictions, nonsense &amp; sacrilegious doctrines</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">But still I would wish to see a more affirmative or<lb/> a more
                rational &amp; comprehensive explanation on the true<lb/> reference of the above
                named &amp; similar prophecies</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I will however not precipitate my opinion &amp;
                <sic>judgement</sic><lb/> on matters of such high importance but endeavour to
                enlighten<lb/> &amp; instruct myself by attentive perusal &amp; study of the
                commentaries<lb/> which you have kindly placed into my hands.</p>
            <p>The Kol<add>?</add>
                <add>יעקב</add> which you have kindly sent me, shall be thankfully<lb/> returned by
                first <add>?</add> opportunity.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I ask your pardon for troubling with so long an epistle<lb/> &amp;
                for <add>?</add> you with such bad English. I do not pre<lb/>sume any sort of
                ability in this branch &amp; have but very little<lb/> time just now to bestow upon
                letter writing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please acknowledge Receipt of the enclosed &amp; receipt the<lb/>
                assurance of my high esteem &amp; deference.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">L. H. Levingston</persName>.</p>
            <p>P. S. You will please to send me No 2. <add>of <date>April</date></add> of the
                Occident,<lb/> which I have never received. I would be glad<lb/> to have this as
                without it some matters in the follo<lb/>wing numbers <del>would</del> could not be
                understood.</p>
        </body>
